cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.LG

The paper discusses the interaction between data centers and the power grid, focusing on load balancing and energy cost reduction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves optimization and control of power systems, which falls under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of pricing mechanisms and algorithms for optimization suggests the involvement of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes both heuristic and robust optimization techniques, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
